                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" width="100%" colspan="2" valign="top">
                  <table width="100%" height="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top">
                      <img src="images/icon_mi_1.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" hspace="3" /><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/03/2003&nbsp;:&nbsp; 4:21:52 PM</font>
                      &nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2195"><img src="images/icon_profile.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Show Profile" title="Show Profile" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=21007&FORUM_ID=2"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Lots of experienced Necros already know this trick, and those who don't solo much can skip it entirely, but for those who don't know.....<br /><br />There is a way to minimize downtime significantly when soloing at level 34  (Call of Bones) all the way to L65.  Lots of necros just pour on the DOTs, get the pet on the mob if fearing or agroing, and watch the mob die, but there is a better idea.  <br /><br />Necros have great Life Taps over time combined with great HPs to Mana illusions especially from CoB onward.  Sooo, only apply enough DOTs along with pet damage (if kiting) until the mob turns, usually at about 12% to 15% or so.  Then pull your pet OFF, and make sure the only DOT left on the mob is Dark.  You don't want the mob to die just yet.  You can keep your low level Dark on the mob so he doesn't go anywhere (or keep him rooted), and just let your CoB, or in my case, Arch Lich, get your mana bar full, reapplying Dark as needed.  Then cast your Life Tap DOT to get your HPs up.  Hopefully the mob still has a percent or two left, so you can continue to convert HPs to mana if needed and then cast another Life Tap DOT.  Remember, you get full HPs from the Life Tap DOT even if the mob only has 5 HPs left.  When you have gotten your mana up as high as the mobs remaining HPs will allow, go ahead and have your pet finish the mob off.<br /><br />Thats it.  <br /><br />In order for this to work well, you might need a HP buff from a cleric or whomever.  I usually keep some Peridots on me and make a donation to get Virtue up for almost 3 hours since I only have about 1450 HPs self buffed.<br /><br />My necro is a L60 currently soloing in PON, and I go non-stop pulling L52-54 mobs.  And... there is something really fun about controlling the last 15% of the mobs life to my benefit.  Why settle for KEI (a measly 14 mana per tick), when Arch Lich gives me 35 mana per tick, as long as I can top off my HPs from the mob!!<br /><br />Anyway, at the risk of getting flamed by those who have known about this for a while, I wanted to make sure that all necros out there know how important reserving the last 15% of the mobs life for YOUR HPs is.  Unless you are at full mana when the mob turns, make sure the mobs last act is to stay alive long enough for you to get your mana bar full, and then give YOU the last 15% of HPs!!  <br /><br />Enjoy... <br /><br /><br /><br /></span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
