                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Yag... answer to your question comes down to playing style.  <br /><br />I like having HPs readily available to me so I can stay in Lich form all the time, without having to go pull at 50% HPs or less, especially when the next pull might resist Dark, and I may end up getting smacked a bit (mobs Im fighting double attack for 300 damage each) before I can get Dark to hold.  So when Im full or nearly full of mana, im also nearly full of HPs before pulling.  <br /><br />I can keep Lich up all the time (faster mana regen) rather than having to click it off when searching for a mob and my HPs gets too low, which means im more vulnerable and not getting mana, plus I have to remember to get back into Lich after the pull.<br /><br />Anyway, it comes down to playing style.  <br /><br />Just  wanted put it out there so those who didn't think about it would at least know and then decide if it matches their playing tactics or not <img src="images/crazy.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" />  <br /><br />Its all good....<br /><br />Ssouless L60<br />E'ci</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
