                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I do it the way the orginal poster does.  I get real low on hps like 10% and then when the mob is close to dieing I leech it.  Then I go grab another.  I do not call off pet for a long period just long enouph for me to cast.  Then for the next pull I am full mana and full health.  I can non stop solo this way and dont die alot.  Today in HoH for the first time I non stopped pulled for 4 hours (only one spec parch, are those things rare or what?) and watched as a nearby necro who was 65 was killing slower than me and he had SoS.  Why would you wait for the next pull?  For the damage the dot does?  I understand that, but if you are lo health you get great agro and dont have to load up on DoTs to get agro or resnare 30 times.  This is just the way I do it, but it works well for me.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
