                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> There's no reason to do any of that stuff if you learn to manage your dots correctly.  Pulling valorians in HoH, just stack the right dots in the right order and you will be FM at the end of the fight.<br /><br />For example.  I pull with Embracing Darkness, Blood of Thule, send pet, Funeral Pyre, Splurt, Dark Plague, recast snare at 55%, Funeral Pyre.  As soon as dark plague runs out, the mob dies and I am at the same mana I started with or higher.  Just find a rhythm and you will do fine.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
